article.headline: Brown 76, Wagner 60
article.story: NEW YORK (AP) -- Jason Forte was 6-of-10 from 3-point range and scored 25 points to lead Brown to its first win of the season, 76-60 over Wagner on Tuesday night. Luke Ruscoe was 4-of-7 on 3s and had 18 points for the Bears (1-4), who finished 13-of-27 from 3-point range. Durell Vinson had 12 points for the Seahawks (1-3), who were 6-for-20 from the free throw line, including 2-for-14 in the second half. Forte had eight points in a 13-2 run that gave Brown a 31-24 lead with 4:02 left in the first half. Wagner responded with 9-2 run that tied it 33-33, but Forte hit a 3 with 46 seconds left that gave Brown a 36-33 halftime lead. After Vinson's layup got Wagner within 53-51 with 9:48 to play, Brown went on another 13-2 run. Marcus Becker had six points and Ruscoe had five in the spurt that gave the Bears a 66-53 lead with 4:41 to play.
